version 2.3.8 2013-08-23

       Minor Update
       New function map.center() to determine the center location of a grid
       in a target coordinate system. Used for better default settins of
       orientation parameter.
       Improvement of R-3 compatibility in rainbow9 and rainbow10.
       (Chrigel Frei)

version 2.3.7 2013-05-08

       Minor Update
       Made amendments to plot.legend() and filled.contour.map() in 
       rep(NULL, ..) statement that produces a warning under R-3.0
       Introduced at.dem.rda in data - a DEM for Austria made by Johann Hiebl.
       Introduced new function plot.austria.map().
       (Chrigel Frei)

version 2.3.6 2013-04-22

       Minor Update
       Introduced non-restrictive NAMESPACE file for working with R-3.0  
       (Chrigel Frei)

version 2.3.5 2012-03-06

       Update
       New world nations boundaries in dataset world.nations.
       Additions to add.map.outlines() to plot the new world
       borders as default.
       Further enlarging clip window in swiss.clip()
       (Chrigel Frei)

version 2.3.4 2012-02-17

       Minor update
       Changed default setting for na.col to grey.
       Amended man-page of plot.alps.map
       Changed swiss.clip() to fully cover the outside with white.
       Changed default settings of plot.alps.map()
       (Chrigel Frei)

version 2.3.3 2011-07-06

       Bug fix and update
       Re-arranged columns in dataset swiss.rain, to work properly with
       plot.points.map.

       Extended options for line width and color in add.map.outlines()
       Corresponding changes to plot.swiss.map() and plot.alps.map()
       Changed default settings for lonlim, latlim, box in plot.alps.map()
       Added thin.map2 argument in add.map.outlines() to allow separate
       thinning for national borders and rivers/lakes. Corresponding
       changes to plot.swiss.map() and plot.alps.map().
       (Chrigel Frei)

version 2.3.2 2010-11-18

       New rivers data set alps.rivers for the Alps. 
       (Francesco Isotta)

version 2.3.1 2010-10-26

       New functions and datasets to plot on Alpine perimeter. 
       New function: plot.alps.map(), modified function: add.map.outlines().
       New datasets: alps.borders, alps.lakes, alps.rivers, expl9, expl10 
       (Francesco Isotta)

version 2.2.1 2010-08-11

       Added algorithm "crossings" in in.polygon.pm, which improves 
       performance of plotting filled contours. 
       (Christoph Frei)

version 2.1.4 2010-06-25

       Rebuild for R-2.11.1
       (Christoph Frei)

version 2.1.3 2010-01-05

       Improved color table prism.colors().
       (Christoph Frei)

version 2.1.2 2009-11-24

       New color table prism.colors().
       (Christoph Frei)

version 2.1.1 2009-10-06

       Corrections to help pages.
       (Christoph Frei)

version 2.1.0 2009-09-09

       Additions/modifications for plotting grids/points/polygons 
       in any geographical coordinate system supported by the geocors
       package. 
       One of the consequences of this is that plot.map necessarily 
       requires that an attribute named "grid.type" is associated
       with the input field, and that attributes specifying the 
       coordinates are given too. 
       These modifications also resulted in a better modularisation
       of the code. Some performance problems remain and need to be 
       resolved at a later stage.
       (Christoph Frei)

       Introduced ptype="plain" to draw a plain map. This replaces
       previous internal procedures where a dummy field was generated
       when fld was NULL or missing.
       (Christoph Frei)

       Bug-fix in plot.legend. Shadings are properly added in the
       legend now.
       (Christoph Frei)

       Bug-fix for plotting map outlines in a global window.
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.2.6 2008-08-18

       Introduced new parameters mar.leg and mar.plot in function
       plot.map().
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.2.5 2008-08-15

       Fixed help page for lonlat2rot. polphi/pollam are lat/lon
       respectively.
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.2.4 2008-08-15

       Bug-fix in plot.points.map color selector for treatment of 
       missing data.
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.2.3 2008-03-19

       Bug in treatment for missing breaks amended in plot.points.map() 
       and plot.poly.map() and plot.map().
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.2.2 2008-03-17

       Allow for automatic setting of breaks in plot.points.map() and 
       plot.poly.map(). Newly introduced parameter nbreaks.
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.2.1 2008-03-06

       Additional examples in plot.points.map().
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.2.0 2008-02-28

       Modified calculation of field range in plot.map() to avoid 
       warning message when entire field is NA. Warning always occurred
       with plot.points.map() because of dummy field.
       (Christoph Frei)

       New function plot.poly.map() for plotting coloured polygons onto
       a map.  
       (Christoph Frei)

       New function plot.points.map() for plotting point symbols or 
       characters onto a map.  
       (Christoph Frei)

       Amended all calls to mapproject - only use list as input. Avoids 
       warning message now occurring with newer versions of R. Changes
       made to image.map(), contour.map(), filled.contour.map(), 
       oplot.map.outlines(), clip.swiss()
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.1.4 2007-10-18

       Some recoding for plot.swiss.map() for more modularity, enabling
       separate overplotting of borders, lakes etc. 
       (Christoph Frei)

version 1.1.2 2006-08-02

       First version (Christoph Frei)

